{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"authorial-hated-blackbear","description":"Wire the two-scope gate posture across all three gates, plumb resolution-class + diagnostic through the verdicts, enforce never-certify-on-degraded structurally, and document the model.\n\n## Why\nThe three gates must share the systemic block-but-retryable posture while PRESERVING per-criterion fail-open, carry the `resolution_class` + `diagnostic` through the verdict/coverage so routing and troubleshooting both work, never sign a degraded result, and tell the human exactly what to do.\n\n## What\n- Systemic failure -> block-but-retryable (exit 11, unsigned) for all three gates: make code-review match plan-review's existing systemic block; turn completion's fail-closed-as-FAIL into a distinct retryable exit (NOT a verification FAIL, which reads as \"your work is wrong\"). PRESERVE plan-review's per-criterion drop-and-continue fail-open (one flaky finder among N must not block the claim).\n- Carry `resolution_class` + `diagnostic` through the three verdict schemas + the `coverage` block; write the diagnostic to the session log for troubleshooting.\n- Structural never-sign guard: the signing path refuses any verdict carrying a `resolution_class` / marked INDETERMINATE (make the illegal state unrepresentable, not per-call-site discipline).\n- Re-check the material fingerprint immediately before signing (retries + timeout widen the verify->sign window; avoid attesting against drifted state). Keep verify strictly OUTSIDE the write lock (`transition_close.py` current ordering must be preserved).\n- Per-class actionable messages; the MCP error shape; exit code 11. Docs: the resolution-disposition taxonomy, the retry/timeout model, and the config keys.\n\n## Scope\n- `gate_dispatch.py` wiring; `transition_close.py` (preserve verify-outside-lock ordering + add pre-sign fingerprint re-check); the verdict JSON schemas; `docs/`.\n- NOT in scope: removing or weakening per-criterion fail-open (must be preserved).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All three gates: a systemic failure -> block-but-retryable, exit 11, unsigned, with a class-specific actionable message.\n- [ ] Per-criterion fail-open is preserved (a single flaky unit among N does not block; regression test).\n- [ ] `resolution_class` + `diagnostic` are plumbed through the verdict schemas + `coverage` + the session log.\n- [ ] The structural never-sign guard rejects signing any degraded/INDETERMINATE verdict; the material fingerprint is re-checked before signing.\n- [ ] Verify remains outside the write lock (ordering preserved; asserted).\n- [ ] Docs updated; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py`, `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py`, `src/rebar/schemas/*.schema.json`, `docs/`.","id":"2eca-0a1d-45c2-4e38","parent_id":"jira-reb-687","priority":2,"tags":["llm-resilience"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Two-scope gate wiring, verdict plumbing, never-sign guard, exit 11, docs"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783557860132682001,"uuid":"d6067e73-6efe-4825-885b-1651e30f60f8"}